Program: The Documentary
Title: Episode 1
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00btwtn
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 21 Nov 2010
For hundreds of years the protest march has been a means of voicing passionate concerns. Whether protesting at injustice, challenging inequalities, fighting for better conditions or showing solidarity for fellow workers - demonstrating has been a way of focusing public anger. While some mass demonstrations have ended in victory, others have led to retreat, defeat and sometimes tragedy. Defying the authorities can be a dangerous business. In this two-part documentary, Michael Goldfarb examines the protest march as a force for change. Show less